{"id":"royal-tree:islamic-atlas:163","names":{"en":"Sultans of Gujarat","tr":"Gücerat Sultanları","ar":"Salātīn Gujarāt"},"country":["AF","BD","IN","PK"],"category":"royal","period":{"founded":null,"extinct":null},"status":"extinct","head_current":null,"sources":["github:alicetinkaya76/islamic-civilization-atlas:all_dynasties_enriched.csv"],"raw":{"atlas_dynasty_id":"163","atlas_name_en_original":"The Sultans of Gujarat","parent_tribe":"Muzafferî ailesi (Tânk Râcpût dönmesi)","ethnic_origin":"Hindistanlı Müslüman (Râcpût dönme)","capital":"Ahmedabad","region_primary":"Gücerat","regions_all":"Ahmedabad; Cambay; Surat; Gücerat","geographic_zone":"Güney Asya","predecessor":"Delhi Sultanlığı valileri","successor":"Bâbürlü Ekber ilhakı","government_type":"Sultanlık|Şahlık","religious_orientation":null,"narrative_en":"The Sultans of Gujarat established a powerful Islamic state centered on Ahmedabad on India's western coast, shaped by maritime trade and Portuguese rivalry. Ahmedabad's architectural legacy forms the most lasting trace of this era.","importance_level":"Normal","capital_lat":"23.02","capital_lon":"72.57","century_start":14,"century_end":16}}
